      • getLengthSquared

        public float getLengthSquared()
        Returns the length of this vector squared

        This method exists because it avoids the square root which makes getLength() slow. If you just need to compare lengths, you can use this method instead.

        Returns:
        the length of this vector, squared
        See Also:
        getLength()

      • getAngle

        public float getAngle()
        Returns the angle between this vector to the X axis

        This method always returns angles between -pi and pi.

        Positive angles are assigned to vectors with positive Y values. This means that if the Y axis points down, increasing the angle moves clockwise. If the Y axis points up, increasing the angle moves anticlockwise.

        Returns:
        the angle of this vector is radians between -pi and pi
        See Also:
        Math.atan2(double, double)

      • getBearing

        public float getBearing()
        Returns the bearing of the vector

        This means that this method returns an angle from 0 to 360 where 0 degrees points upwards (positive y direction).

        Returns:
        the bearing of this vector

      • equals

        public final boolean equals(Vector2D other)
        Returns true if this vector is exactly equal to another

        You probably DO NOT want to be calling this method.

        Due to floating point rounding errors, this method is slightly dangerous and can return values you might not expect.

        Parameters:
        other - other vector to compare
        Returns:
        true if x and y are equal in both vectors
